                <h1>Does Quitting a Job Affect Your Record? Insights Revealed</h1>
                <p>Quitting a job typically does not go on your formal employment record. However, it may be mentioned in references or background checks if an employer discloses that information. It's important to resign professionally to maintain good relationships and to ensure future employers have a positive impression of your work history.</p>
